<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 4:21PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern Moore,
Montgomery, southern Randolph and eastern Stanly Counties through 515
PM EDT...
At 421 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Badin Lake to 6 miles south of Plyler.
Movement was east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Troy, Badin Lake, Biscoe, Seagrove, Norwood, Badin,
Oakboro, Mount Gilead and Star.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
